[48.45647499999999, "o", "\u001b[1G\u001b[J\u001b[32m\u25c7\u001b[39m  \r\n\u001b[?25h"]
[48.45704899999999, "o", "\r\n\u001b[32m\u2714\u001b[39m \u001b[92m\u001b[1mDone\u001b[22m\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n"]
[48.49886899999999, "o", "\u001b[95m  \u256d \u001b[95m\u2b21 Orbis AI\u001b[39m\u001b[95m \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u256e\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0mI have enough information to give you a comprehensive overview.\u001b[0m                                                                                      \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[32m\u001b[1m## Alphabet Inc. \u2014 Google's Parent Company\u001b[22m\u001b[39m                                                                                                           \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0m\u001b[1mWhat it is:\u001b[22m Alphabet Inc. is an American technology conglomerate and holding company, widely known as \"Google's parent                               \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   company.\" It was formed in 2015 through a major corporate restructuring of Google and its various subsidiaries.\u001b[0m                                      \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0m\u001b[1mWhy it was created:\u001b[22m Co-founders Larry Page and Sergey Brin announced the change to allow Google to pursue \"moonshots\"                                \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   and diversify beyond its core search business into industries like healthcare, robotics, transportation, and AI \u2014 while                              \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   keeping the main Google business focused. Page explained the name: \"Alphabet\" represents a collection of letters                                     \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   (language, the basis of Google Search) and is a pun on \u001b[1m\"alpha-bet\"\u001b[22m (alpha = investment return above benchmark), which                                \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   they strive for. He also stressed the goal of improving \"transparency and oversight.\"\u001b[0m                                                                \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0m\u001b[1mCorporate structure:\u001b[22m Alphabet replaced Google Inc. as the publicly traded entity. Google became a wholly-owned                                       \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   subsidiary, and all Google shares automatically converted into Alphabet shares (trading on Nasdaq as \u001b[1mGOOGL\u001b[22m and \u001b[1mGOOG\u001b[22m).                                \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   Leadership: Larry Page became CEO of Alphabet, Sergey Brin President, and Sundar Pichai became CEO of Google. Today,                                 \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   Pichai serves as CEO of Alphabet itself.\u001b[0m                                                                                                             \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[32m\u001b[1m### Business segments\u001b[22m\u001b[39m "]
[48.49915699999999, "o", "                                                                                                                               \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0mAlphabet organizes its operations into three main segments:\u001b[0m                                                                                          \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   1. \u001b[0m**Google Services** \u2014 the core and largest segment (~92% of revenue as of 2022). Includes Search, advertising, Android, Chrome, Google Maps,      \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   Google Play, YouTube, and Gemini (generative AI chatbot).\u001b[0m                                                                                            \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   2. \u001b[0m**Google Cloud** \u2014 enterprise cloud computing solutions for businesses and governments (~7% of revenue).\u001b[0m                                          \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   3. \u001b[0m**Other Bets** \u2014 emerging-stage ventures (~1% of revenue), such as:                                                                               \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m\u001b[0m**Waymo** (self-driving cars)\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                      \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0m                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m\u001b[0m**Calico** (biotech/longevity research)\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\u001b[0m                                                                                                            \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0m                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m\u001b[0m**DeepMind** (AI research)\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                         \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0m                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m\u001b[0m**Nest** (smart-home devices)\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                      \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0m                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m\u001b[0m**CapitalG** (private equity)\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                      \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0m                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m\u001b[0m**X** (the \"moonshot factory,\" e.g., Wing drone delivery)\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\u001b[0m                                                                                          \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[32m\u001b[1m### Strategic rationale\u001b[22m\u001b[39m                                                                                                                              \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                         "]
[48.499221999999996, "o", "                                               \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m**Risk management** \u2014 separating brands/operations lets Alphabet pursue risky ventures while shielding the core Google brand from reputational     \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   damage.\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                              \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m**Financial transparency** \u2014 segment reporting lets investors distinguish the performance of Search/ads from YouTube, Cloud, Waymo, etc.\u001b[0m           \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m**Antitrust mitigation** \u2014 presenting each company as operating independently of the search engine helps reduce regulatory glare.\u001b[0m                  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m**Founder control** \u2014 the dual-class share structure lets Page and Brin retain majority voting power without majority ownership, protecting the    \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   long-term vision from short-term investor pressure.\u001b[0m                                                                                                  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[32m\u001b[1m### Scale (recent figures from Britannica)\u001b[22m\u001b[39m                                                                                                           \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m**Ticker:** GOOGL\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m**Market cap:** ~$4.39 trillion\u001b[0m                                                                                                                    \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m**Annual revenue:** ~$422.5 billion\u001b[0m                                                                                                                \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   * \u001b[0m**CEO:** Sundar Pichai\u001b[0m                                                                                                                             \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[32m\u001b[1m### In short\u001b[22m\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                         \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0mAlphabet is the holding company that owns Google and a sprawling collection of semi-autonomous companies. Its structure                              \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   lets a focused Google run the lucrative search/ads/cloud businesses while \"Other Bets\" experiment with the future \u2014                                  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   self-driving cars, life-extension science, AI research, and more \u2014 all under shared resources and capital.\u001b[0m                                           \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m   \u001b[0m\u001b[1mSources:\u001b[22m abc.xyz (Larry Page's original founder letter), Britannica, and Investopedia.\u001b[0m                                                               \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[95m\u2502\u001b[39m                                                         "]
